# ============================================================
# Time Lag Calculation and Global Analysis - Full-pixel rigorous version
# 修正版：只使用 LSTD daytime LST，不混入 LSTN nighttime LST
#
# Purpose:
#   Quantify seasonal alignment between remotely sensed land-surface
#   phenology (LSP; EVI trajectory) and rapid daytime surface warming
#   (LSTD trajectory) across global cities.
#
# Key methodological choices:
#   1) No manual koppen_map.
#      Uses selected_cities_fullinfo_with_koppen.xlsx generated from
#      standard Köppen–Geiger 1991–2020 raster.
#
#   2) Explicit lag definition:
#         lag = t_heat - t_LSP
#      Positive lag means LSP activation precedes rapid surface warming.
#
#   3) Only daytime LST bands labelled LSTD_* are used.
#      Nighttime LST bands labelled LSTN_* are excluded.
#
#   4) No random pixel cap by default.
#      All pixels within the NTL-filtered urban analysis mask are used.
#
#   5) NTL mask is a fixed contemporary urban analysis domain.
#      It is not interpreted as a dynamic annual urban boundary.
#
#   6) City-year statistics are calculated first.
#      City-level statistics are then year-balanced.
#
#   7) No peak fallback by default.
#      Pixels without stable onset in either EVI or LSTD are excluded.
# ============================================================

